<title>AUSTRALIA: Polartechnics shares soar on U.S. alliance.</title>
<headline>Polartechnics shares soar on U.S. alliance.</headline>
<dateline>SYDNEY 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in medical instrument designer Polartechnics Ltd rose after news that it formed an alliance with U.S. pharmaceutical group Johnson &amp; Johnson to commercialise its cancer detection device.</p>
<p>At 11.15 a.m. (0115 GMT), Polartechnics shares were 57 cents or 22.98 percent higher at A$3.05 cents, just off its earlier high of A$3.30. Just over 78,000 shares were traded.</p>
